parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and potentially lead to accidents, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls while driving
sometimes without warning
and may not restart immediately. The vehicle may shake or vibrate before stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, stalling, and potentially causing fires.
symptoms: The temperature gauge goes up
the engine overheats
and smoke or flames may come from the engine area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design flaw in the muffler can cause corrosion of the left rear suspension bars, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Fumes emitting from the muffler
corrosion of the left rear suspension bars
and the muffler drain hole is on top.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the pulley and crankshaft can cause the engine to stall, overheat, and potentially lead to engine damage.
symptoms: The engine makes a loud knocking noise
the crankshaft pulley is loose
and the engine may stall or overheat.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Gas Tank and Fuel System Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gas tank and fuel system can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Gas tank is leaking
fuel is spraying back onto the muffler
and fumes are present in the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine head gasket can cause fluid leaks, engine damage, and potentially lead to engine failure.
symptoms: Fluid is leaking from the engine
and the engine head gasket is blown.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The service engine warning light can indicate a problem with the engine, which if not addressed, can lead to engine damage and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: The service engine warning light is illuminated
and the vehicle may stall or have difficulty starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized seatbelt can cause the seatbelt to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or even fatalities. In some cases, the seatbelt may tighten excessively, causing choking or constriction.
symptoms: The seatbelt tightens excessively
becomes stuck
or fails to retract
causing difficulty moving or breathing. The seatbelt may also malfunction during an accident
failing to provide adequate protection.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt retractor can cause the seatbelt to become stuck or inoperable, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The seatbelt retractor fails to function
causing the seatbelt to become stuck or jammed. The seatbelt may also fail to retract
making it difficult to move or exit the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic shoulder belt can cause the seatbelt to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or even fatalities.
symptoms: The automatic shoulder belt fails to function
causing the seatbelt to become stuck or inoperable. The seatbelt may also malfunction during an accident
failing to provide adequate protection.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt track can cause the seatbelt to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or even fatalities.
symptoms: The seatbelt track fails to function
causing the seatbelt to become stuck or jammed. The seatbelt may also fail to retract
making it difficult to move or exit the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting and corrosion of the fuel tank can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, and accidents. Additionally, fuel leaks can also cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Fuel odor
fuel leaks
rust or corrosion on the fuel tank
fuel tank rupture
fuel leakage onto hot exhaust pipes
vehicle stalling or shutting off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle stalling or shutting off while driving
engine check light illuminating
fuel pump overheating
vehicle unable to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the carburetor and distributor can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle stalling or shutting off while driving
engine check light illuminating
carburetor and distributor failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the control arm can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents.
symptoms: Rust or corrosion on the control arm
breakage of the control arm
loss of vehicle control.
